rook.api.collections

Interface ThreadSafeCollection<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T -
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AtomicCollection, SynchronizedCollection

    public interface ThreadSafeCollection<T>
    Thread safe collection with built-in List<>, Set<>, and Dequeue<> functionality.
    Author:
    Eric Thill

        boolean add(T e,
            boolean allowDup)
        Add an element to the collection
        Parameters:
        e - The element to add
        allowDup - If a duplicate of this element is allowed. False -> Set functionality, True -> List functionality.
        Returns:
        True if added, False otherwise. False can only be returned when allowDup=false.
